# MCP Tool Development

## Tool Registration
Use `createToolRegistrar()` from `@mcp-stack/core`:
```typescript
import { createToolRegistrar } from '@mcp-stack/core'
const register = createToolRegistrar(server, logger, auditLogger)
register('tool_name', 'Description', { inputSchema }, handler)
```
This gives you: auto error handling, timing, audit logging — for free.

## Tool Design Principles
- Each tool does ONE thing well
- Names: snake_case, verb-first (`search_documents`, `add_meter_reading`)
- Descriptions: explain WHAT the tool does AND WHEN to use it
- Input schemas: use required fields sparingly, prefer sensible defaults
- Return structured JSON — let Claude interpret, don't write prose
- Include pagination for list operations

## Unified Tool Pattern (CenterDevice precedent)
Merge batch + single operations into one tool that accepts one-or-many:
- Single input: `{ documentId: "abc" }` or `{ documentIds: ["abc"] }`
- Internally pick the most efficient API strategy (parallel exec vs native bulk)
- See `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` → "Unified Tools" for the full mapping

## API Client Pattern
Each package has a `client.ts` that:
- Wraps the external API with typed methods
- Handles auth headers, base URLs, content types
- Returns typed responses, throws on HTTP errors
- Documents API quirks inline (see ARCHITECTURE.md for known quirks)

## CenterDevice Specifics
- Tag operations: `add_tags` BEFORE `remove_tags` (order matters)
- File operations order: rename → move → tag (DATEV locks after move)
- `copy_document` does NOT inherit tags — apply separately
- `/` not allowed in folder names — use `+` as substitute
- `move_to_folders` doesn't cross collections — use collection add/remove instead

## Bidrento Specifics
- POST bodies are `application/x-www-form-urlencoded` (not JSON)
- `list_invoices` returns 404 when empty — client returns `[]`
- Buildings/units are read-only via API (create in web UI only)

## Error Responses
Always return structured errors:
```typescript
{ error: 'Document not found', code: 'NOT_FOUND', details: { documentId } }
```
Never let raw API errors bubble to Claude unhandled.

## Write Operations
All write tools must:
- Be logged via audit logger
- Accept a `reason` parameter for destructive ops (delete, move, rename, split)
- Return confirmation of what was changed
